  "doc_id": "13638",
  "text": "Because both Precision and Recall have their biases, this study focuses on the F1 score. Since it is extremely difficult for the pixel-level ground truth to be obtained by crack images, a tolerance margin is used in most crack detection algorithms for evaluating the performance of the algorithm. This margin takes into account detected pixels that are no more than 2 [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] or 5 [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] pixels away from the ground truth as the TP. We use a tolerance margin of 2 pixels in this study.",
